# Optimal Solution

## Main Idea

Instead of calculating the path multiple times,

calculate it **once** using **Postorder DFS**.

Each node returns

> Longest consecutive path **starting from itself**.

Its parent will use this answer.

Every subtree is solved only once.

---

# Intuition

Suppose

```
      5
     /
    6
   /
  7
```

When DFS reaches

```
7
```

It knows

```
answer =1
```

